<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="340" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d340">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 102.62/50</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Swiss Legation</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <p rend="center">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                        </p>
                        <p>The Department of State returns, herewith, the patent documents received
                            with the memorandum of the Legation of Switzerland (X–c–19), Department
                            of German Interests, dated May 9, 1917,<note n="1" xml:id="d340fn1">Not
                                printed.</note> and states that because of the state of war existing
                            between the United States and Germany, the Department cannot transmit to
                            the Commissioner of Patents papers relating to the patent applications
                            of German subjects.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline rendition="#left">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-18"><hi rend="italic">May 18, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>